[{"text": "My topic", "start": 15.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "is economic growth in China and India.", "start": 17.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "And the question I want to explore with you", "start": 20.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "is whether or not", "start": 23.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "democracy has helped or has hindered", "start": 25.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "economic growth.", "start": 28.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "You may say this is not fair,", "start": 30.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "because I'm selecting two countries", "start": 32.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "to make a case against democracy.", "start": 35.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Actually, exactly the opposite", "start": 38.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "is what I'm going to do.", "start": 41.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "I'm going to use these two countries", "start": 43.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "to make an economic argument for democracy,", "start": 45.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "rather than against democracy.", "start": 48.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "The first question there", "start": 51.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "is why China has grown so much faster", "start": 53.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "than India.", "start": 55.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Over the last 30 years,", "start": 57.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "in terms of the GDP growth rates,", "start": 59.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "China has grown at twice the rate of India.", "start": 62.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "In the last five years,", "start": 66.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "the two countries have begun to converge somewhat", "start": 68.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "in economic growth.", "start": 71.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "But over the last 30 years,", "start": 73.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "China undoubtedly", "start": 75.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "has done much better than India.", "start": 77.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "One simple answer", "start": 80.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "is China has Shanghai and India has Mumbai.", "start": 82.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Look at the skyline of Shanghai.", "start": 85.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "This is the Pudong area.", "start": 88.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "The picture on India", "start": 90.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "is the Dharavi slum of Mumbai", "start": 92.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "in India.", "start": 94.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "The idea there", "start": 96.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "behind these two pictures", "start": 98.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "is that the Chinese government", "start": 100.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "can act above rule of law.", "start": 102.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "It can plan", "start": 104.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "for the long-term benefits of the country", "start": 106.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and in the process,", "start": 108.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "evict millions of people --", "start": 110.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "that's just a small technical issue.", "start": 112.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Whereas in India, you cannot do that,", "start": 115.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "because you have to listen to the public.", "start": 117.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "You're being constrained by the public's opinion.", "start": 120.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Even Prime Minister Manmohan Singh", "start": 122.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "agrees with that view.", "start": 125.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "In an interview", "start": 127.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "printed in the financial press of India,", "start": 129.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "He said that he wants to make Mumbai", "start": 131.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "another Shanghai.", "start": 134.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "This is an Oxford-trained economist", "start": 136.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "steeped in humanistic values,", "start": 139.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "and yet he agrees", "start": 143.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "with the high-pressure tactics of Shanghai.", "start": 145.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "So let me call it the Shanghai model of economic growth,", "start": 149.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "that emphasizes the following features", "start": 152.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "for promoting economic development:", "start": 156.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "infrastructures, airports,", "start": 158.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "highways, bridges, things like that.", "start": 160.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "And you need a strong government to do that,", "start": 163.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "because you cannot respect private property rights.", "start": 166.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "You cannot be constrained by the public's opinion.", "start": 169.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "You need also state ownership,", "start": 172.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "especially of land assets,", "start": 174.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "in order to build and roll out infrastructures", "start": 177.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "very quickly.", "start": 180.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "The implication of that model", "start": 182.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "is that democracy", "start": 184.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "is a hindrance for economic growth,", "start": 186.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "rather than a facilitator of economic growth.", "start": 188.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "Here's the key question.", "start": 192.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Just how important are infrastructures", "start": 194.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "for economic growth?", "start": 197.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "This is a key issue.", "start": 199.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "If you believe that infrastructures are very important for economic growth,", "start": 201.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "then you would argue a strong government is necessary", "start": 205.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "to promote growth.", "start": 208.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "If you believe", "start": 210.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "that infrastructures are not as important as many people believe,", "start": 212.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "then you will put less emphasis", "start": 215.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "on strong government.", "start": 217.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "So to illustrate that question,", "start": 219.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "let me give you two countries.", "start": 221.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "And for the sake of brevity,", "start": 223.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "I'll call one country Country 1", "start": 225.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and the other country Country 2.", "start": 227.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Country 1", "start": 229.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "has a systematic advantage over Country 2", "start": 231.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "in infrastructures.", "start": 234.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Country 1 has more telephones,", "start": 236.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "and Country 1 has a longer system of railways.", "start": 239.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "So if I were to ask you,", "start": 242.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "\"Which is China", "start": 245.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and which is India,", "start": 247.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and which country has grown faster?\"", "start": 249.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "if you believe in the infrastructure view,", "start": 251.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "then you will say, \"Country 1 must be China.", "start": 254.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "They must have done better, in terms of economic growth.", "start": 257.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "And Country 2 is possibly India.\"", "start": 259.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "Actually the country with more telephones", "start": 263.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "is the Soviet Union,", "start": 266.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and the data referred to 1989.", "start": 268.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "After the country reported very impressive statistics on telephones,", "start": 271.26, "duration": 5.0}, {"text": "the country collapsed.", "start": 276.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "That's not too good.", "start": 279.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "The picture there is Khrushchev.", "start": 281.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "I know that in 1989", "start": 283.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "he no longer ruled the Soviet Union,", "start": 285.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "but that's the best picture that I can find.", "start": 287.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "(Laughter)", "start": 290.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Telephones, infrastructures", "start": 292.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "do not guarantee you economic growth.", "start": 294.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Country 2, that has fewer telephones,", "start": 296.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "is China.", "start": 299.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Since 1989,", "start": 301.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "the country has performed at a double-digit rate", "start": 303.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "every year for the last 20 years.", "start": 305.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "If you know nothing about China and the Soviet Union", "start": 308.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "other than the fact about their telephones,", "start": 311.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "you would have made a poor prediction", "start": 314.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "about their economic growth", "start": 316.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "in the next two decades.", "start": 318.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Country 1, that has a longer system of railways,", "start": 320.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "is actually India.", "start": 323.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "And Country 2 is China.", "start": 325.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "This is a very little known fact", "start": 328.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "about the two countries.", "start": 331.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Yes, today China has a huge infrastructure advantage", "start": 333.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "over India.", "start": 335.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "But for many years,", "start": 337.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "until the late 1990s,", "start": 339.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "China had an infrastructure disadvantage", "start": 341.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "vis-a-vis India.", "start": 343.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "In developing countries,", "start": 345.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "the most common mode of transportation", "start": 347.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "is the railways,", "start": 350.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and the British built a lot of railways in India.", "start": 352.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "India is the smaller of the two countries,", "start": 355.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "and yet it had a longer system of railways", "start": 358.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "until the late 1990s.", "start": 361.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "So clearly,", "start": 363.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "infrastructure doesn't explain", "start": 365.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "why China did better before the late 1990s,", "start": 367.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "as compared with India.", "start": 370.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "In fact, if you look at the evidence worldwide,", "start": 372.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "the evidence is more supportive of the view", "start": 376.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "that the infrastructure are actually the result of economic growth.", "start": 379.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "The economy grows,", "start": 383.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "government accumulates more resources,", "start": 385.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and the government can invest in infrastructure --", "start": 387.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "rather than infrastructure being a cause", "start": 390.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "for economic growth.", "start": 393.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "And this is clearly the story", "start": 395.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "of the Chinese economic growth.", "start": 397.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Let me look at this question more directly.", "start": 400.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Is democracy bad for economic growth?", "start": 402.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Now let's turn to two countries,", "start": 405.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Country A and Country B.", "start": 407.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Country A, in 1990,", "start": 410.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "had about $300 per capita GDP", "start": 412.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "as compared with Country B,", "start": 415.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "which had $460 in per capita GDP.", "start": 417.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "By 2008,", "start": 420.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Country A has surpassed Country B", "start": 422.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "with $700 per capita GDP", "start": 425.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "as compared with $650 per capita GDP.", "start": 428.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "Both countries are in Asia.", "start": 432.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "If I were to ask you,", "start": 434.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "\"Which are the two Asian countries?", "start": 436.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "And which one is a democracy?\"", "start": 438.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "you may argue,", "start": 440.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "\"Well, maybe Country A is China", "start": 442.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and Country B is India.\"", "start": 444.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "In fact, Country A", "start": 446.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "is democratic India,", "start": 448.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and Country B is Pakistan --", "start": 450.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "the country that has a long period", "start": 453.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "of military rule.", "start": 455.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "And it's very common", "start": 457.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "that we compare India with China.", "start": 459.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "That's because the two countries", "start": 463.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "have about the same population size.", "start": 465.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "But the more natural comparison", "start": 468.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "is actually between India and Pakistan.", "start": 470.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Those two countries are geographically similar.", "start": 472.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "They have a complicated, but shared common history.", "start": 475.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "By that comparison,", "start": 479.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "democracy looks very, very good", "start": 481.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "in terms of economic growth.", "start": 483.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "So why do economists fall in love", "start": 486.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "with authoritarian governments?", "start": 489.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "One reason is the East Asian Model.", "start": 492.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "In East Asia,", "start": 494.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "we have had successful economic growth stories", "start": 496.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "such as Korea, Taiwan,", "start": 499.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Hong Kong and Singapore.", "start": 501.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Some of these economies", "start": 503.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "were ruled by authoritarian governments", "start": 505.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "in the 60s and 70s", "start": 507.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and 1980s.", "start": 509.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "The problem with that view", "start": 511.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "is like asking all the winners of lotteries,", "start": 513.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "\"Have you won the lottery?\"", "start": 516.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "And they all tell you, \"Yes, we have won the lottery.\"", "start": 519.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "And then you draw the conclusion", "start": 521.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "the odds of winning the lottery", "start": 523.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "are 100 percent.", "start": 526.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "The reason is you never go", "start": 528.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and bother to ask the losers", "start": 530.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "who also purchased lottery tickets", "start": 532.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and didn't end up winning the prize.", "start": 534.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "For each of these successful authoritarian governments", "start": 538.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "in East Asia,", "start": 541.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "there's a matched failure.", "start": 543.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Korea succeeded, North Korea didn't.", "start": 546.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Taiwan succeeded, China under Mao Zedong didn't.", "start": 549.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Burma didn't succeed.", "start": 552.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "The Philippines didn't succeed.", "start": 554.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "If you look at the statistical evidence worldwide,", "start": 556.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "there's really no support for the idea", "start": 559.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "that authoritarian governments", "start": 562.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "hold a systematic edge over democracies", "start": 564.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "in terms of economic growth.", "start": 567.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "So the East Asian model", "start": 569.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "has this massive selection bias --", "start": 571.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "it is known as selecting on a dependent variable,", "start": 573.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "something we always tell our students to avoid.", "start": 576.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "So exactly why did China grow so much faster?", "start": 580.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "I will take you to the Cultural Revolution,", "start": 585.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "when China went mad,", "start": 587.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and compare that country's performance with India", "start": 589.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "under Indira Gandhi.", "start": 592.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "The question there is: Which country did better,", "start": 594.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "China or India?", "start": 597.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "China was during the Cultural Revolution.", "start": 599.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "It turns out even during the Cultural Revolution,", "start": 601.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "China out-perfomed India", "start": 603.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "in terms of GDP growth", "start": 605.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "by an average of about 2.2 percent every year", "start": 607.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "in terms of per capita GDP.", "start": 610.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "So that's when China was mad.", "start": 613.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "The whole country went mad.", "start": 615.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "It must mean that the country", "start": 618.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "had something so advantageous to itself in terms of economic growth", "start": 620.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "to overcome the negative effects", "start": 624.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "of the Cultural Revolution.", "start": 627.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "The advantage the country had", "start": 629.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "was human capital --", "start": 631.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "nothing else but human capital.", "start": 634.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "This is the world development index indicator data", "start": 636.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "in the early 1990s.", "start": 640.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "And this is the earliest data that I can find.", "start": 642.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "The adult literacy rate in China", "start": 645.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "is 77 percent", "start": 648.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "as compared with 48 percent in India.", "start": 650.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "The contrast in literacy rates", "start": 653.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "is especially sharp", "start": 656.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "between Chinese women and Indian women.", "start": 658.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "I haven't told you about the definition of literacy.", "start": 661.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "In China, the definition of literacy", "start": 665.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "is the ability to read and write", "start": 668.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "1,500 Chinese characters.", "start": 670.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "In India, the definition of literacy,", "start": 673.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "operating definition of literacy,", "start": 676.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "is the ability, the grand ability,", "start": 678.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "to write your own name", "start": 681.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "in whatever language you happen to speak.", "start": 683.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "The gap between the two countries in terms of literacy", "start": 687.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "is much more substantial", "start": 689.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "than the data here indicated.", "start": 691.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "If you go to other sources of data", "start": 694.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "such as Human Development Index,", "start": 696.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "that data series,", "start": 698.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "go back to the early 1970s,", "start": 700.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "you see exactly the same contrast.", "start": 703.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "China held a huge advantage", "start": 705.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "in terms of human capital", "start": 707.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "vis-a-vis India.", "start": 709.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Life expectancies:", "start": 711.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "as early as 1965,", "start": 713.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "China had a huge advantage in life expectancy.", "start": 715.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "On average, as a Chinese in 1965,", "start": 719.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "you lived 10 years more", "start": 722.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "than an average Indian.", "start": 724.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "So if you have a choice", "start": 726.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "between being a Chinese and being an Indian,", "start": 728.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "you would want to become a Chinese", "start": 730.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "in order to live 10 years longer.", "start": 732.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "If you made that decision in 1965,", "start": 735.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "the down side of that", "start": 737.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "is the next year we have the Cultural Revolution.", "start": 739.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "So you have to always think carefully", "start": 741.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "about these decisions.", "start": 744.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "If you cannot chose your nationality,", "start": 746.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "then you will want to become an Indian man.", "start": 749.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Because, as an Indian man,", "start": 752.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "you have about two years of life expectancy advantage", "start": 754.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "vis-a-vis Indian women.", "start": 757.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "This is an extremely strange fact.", "start": 760.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "It's very rare among countries", "start": 763.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "to have this kind of pattern.", "start": 766.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "It shows the systematic discrimination and biases", "start": 768.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "in the Indian society", "start": 771.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "against women.", "start": 773.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "The good news is, by 2006,", "start": 775.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "India has closed the gap", "start": 777.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "between men and women", "start": 779.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "in terms of life expectancy.", "start": 781.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Today, Indian women have a sizable life expectancy edge", "start": 784.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "over Indian men.", "start": 787.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "So India is reverting to the normal.", "start": 789.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "But India still has a lot of work to do", "start": 792.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "in terms of gender equality.", "start": 794.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "These are the two pictures", "start": 796.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "taken of garment factories in Guangdong Province", "start": 798.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "and garment factories in India.", "start": 801.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "In China, it's all women.", "start": 804.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "60 to 80 percent of the workforce in China is women", "start": 806.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "in the coastal part of the country,", "start": 809.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "whereas in India, it's all men.", "start": 811.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Financial Times printed this picture", "start": 814.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "of an Indian textile factory", "start": 816.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "with the title, \"India Poised to Overtake China in Textile.\"", "start": 818.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "By looking at these two pictures,", "start": 822.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "I say no, it won't overtake China for a while.", "start": 824.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "If you look at other East Asian countries,", "start": 828.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "women there play a hugely important role", "start": 830.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "in terms of economic take-off --", "start": 834.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "in terms of creating the manufacturing miracle", "start": 836.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "associated with East Asia.", "start": 839.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "India still has a long way to go", "start": 841.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "to catch up with China.", "start": 843.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Then the issue is,", "start": 845.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "what about the Chinese political system?", "start": 847.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "You talk about human capital,", "start": 849.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "you talk about education and public health.", "start": 851.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "What about the political system?", "start": 853.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Isn't it true that the one-party political system", "start": 855.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "has facilitated economic growth in China?", "start": 858.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "Actually, the answer is more nuanced and subtle than that.", "start": 862.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "It depends on a distinction that you draw", "start": 866.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "between statics of the political system", "start": 869.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "and the dynamics of the political system.", "start": 872.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Statically, China is a one-party system,", "start": 874.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "authoritarian -- there's no question about it.", "start": 877.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Dynamically, it has changed over time", "start": 880.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "to become less authoritarian and more democratic.", "start": 883.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "When you explain change --", "start": 886.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "for example, economic growth;", "start": 888.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "economic growth is about change --", "start": 890.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "when you explain change,", "start": 892.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "you use other things that have changed to explain change,", "start": 894.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "rather than using the constant to explain change.", "start": 897.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "Sometimes a fixed effect can explain change,", "start": 901.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "but a fixed effect only explains changes", "start": 904.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "in interaction with the things that change.", "start": 907.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "In terms of the political changes,", "start": 910.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "they have introduced village elections.", "start": 912.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "They have increased the security of proprietors.", "start": 914.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "And they have increased the security", "start": 918.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "with long-term land leases.", "start": 921.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "There are also financial reforms in rural China.", "start": 923.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "There is also a rural entrepreneurial revolution in China.", "start": 926.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "To me, the pace of political changes", "start": 929.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "is too slow, too gradual.", "start": 932.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "And my own view is the country", "start": 934.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "is going to face some substantial challenges,", "start": 936.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "because they have not moved further and faster on political reforms.", "start": 938.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "But nevertheless,", "start": 942.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "the system has moved in a more liberal direction,", "start": 944.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "moved in a more democratic direction.", "start": 947.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "You can apply exactly the same dynamic perspective on India.", "start": 951.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "In fact, when India was growing", "start": 955.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "at a Hindu rate of growth --", "start": 957.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "about one percent, two percent a year --", "start": 959.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "that was when India was least democratic.", "start": 961.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Indira Gandhi declared emergency rule in 1975.", "start": 964.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "The Indian government owned and operated", "start": 968.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "all the TV stations.", "start": 971.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "A little-known fact about India in the 1990s", "start": 973.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "is that the country", "start": 976.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "not only has undertaken economic reforms,", "start": 978.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "the country has also undertaken political reforms", "start": 981.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "by introducing village self-rule,", "start": 984.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "privatization of media", "start": 987.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "and introducing freedom of information acts.", "start": 990.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "So the dynamic perspective", "start": 994.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "fits both with China and in India", "start": 996.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "in terms of the direction.", "start": 998.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Why do many people believe", "start": 1000.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "that India is still a growth disaster?", "start": 1003.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "One reason", "start": 1006.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "is they are always comparing India with China.", "start": 1008.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "But China is a superstar", "start": 1011.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "in terms of economic growth.", "start": 1013.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "If you are a NBA player", "start": 1015.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and you are always being compared to Michael Jordan,", "start": 1017.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "you're going to look not so impressive.", "start": 1020.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "But that doesn't mean", "start": 1022.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "that you're a bad basketball player.", "start": 1024.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Comparing with a superstar", "start": 1026.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "is the wrong benchmark.", "start": 1028.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "In fact, if you compare India", "start": 1030.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "with the average developing country,", "start": 1032.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "even before the more recent period", "start": 1034.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "of acceleration of Indian growth --", "start": 1037.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "now India is growing between eight and nine percent --", "start": 1039.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "even before this period,", "start": 1042.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "India was ranked fourth in terms of economic growth", "start": 1044.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "among emerging economies.", "start": 1047.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "This is a very impressive record indeed.", "start": 1050.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Let's think about the future:", "start": 1054.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "the dragon vis-a-vis the elephant.", "start": 1056.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Which country has the growth momentum?", "start": 1059.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "China, I believe, still has", "start": 1062.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "some of the excellent raw fundamentals --", "start": 1065.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "mostly the social capital,", "start": 1068.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "the public health,", "start": 1070.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "the sense of egalitarianism", "start": 1072.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "that you don't find in India.", "start": 1074.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "But I believe that India has the momentum.", "start": 1076.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "It has the improving fundamentals.", "start": 1078.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "The government has invested in basic education,", "start": 1080.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "has invested in basic health.", "start": 1083.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "I believe the government should do more,", "start": 1085.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "but nevertheless, the direction it is moving in", "start": 1087.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "is the right direction.", "start": 1089.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "India has the right institutional conditions", "start": 1091.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "for economic growth,", "start": 1094.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "whereas China is still struggling", "start": 1096.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "with political reforms.", "start": 1098.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "I believe that the political reforms are a must for China", "start": 1100.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "to maintain its growth.", "start": 1103.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "And it's very important to have political reforms,", "start": 1106.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "to have widely shared benefits of economic growth.", "start": 1108.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "I don't know whether that's going to happen or not,", "start": 1111.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "but I'm an optimist.", "start": 1113.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Hopefully, five years from now, I'm going to report to TEDGlobal", "start": 1115.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "that political reforms will happen in China.", "start": 1118.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Thank you very much.", "start": 1120.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "(Applause)", "start": 1122.26, "duration": 3.0}]